<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="reception-n">reception <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /rɪ'sepʃn/    美 /rɪ'sepʃn/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1c">1.<strong>[C] [常用单数] 接待；欢迎；反响：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He got <strong>a warm reception</strong> from the crowd. 
他受到了人群的热烈欢迎。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>His latest album has <strong>met with mixed reception</strong> from fans. 
歌迷对他的最新专辑反响各异。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-u">2.★ <strong>[U] 接待处；前台：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Please leave your key at the <strong>reception desk</strong>. 
请把你的钥匙放在前台。</p></div>

<h4 id="3c">3.<strong>[C] 招待会；欢迎会；宴会：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a wedding reception
婚宴</p></div>

<h4 id="4u">4.<strong>[U] (无线电等的) 接收效果：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>There was very <strong>poor reception</strong> on my cell phone.
我手机的信号很差。</p></div></div>